data.description:
Welcome to your dream home in Sulphur, Oklahoma, where nature and comfort harmonize perfectly. This exceptional property sits on a secluded dead-end street, surrounded by Chickasaw Nation land and the national park, within 2 miles of Arbuckle Lake.

Upon entering, you'll be struck by the attention to detail and modern amenities. The chef's kitchen boasts a commercial sized refrigerator, large island with an ice machine, complemented by elegant quartz countertops. The inviting living room features cathedral ceilings with beams and a cozy wood-burning fireplace, while the home's spray foam insulation ensures year-round comfort and low utility bills.

A standout feature is the fully furnished studio on the second level, which includes a kitchen, living room, bedroom  full bath and laundry area.  This could be a potential income source as a short term rental, a comfortable space for guests to enjoy or simply utilized as additional living for the homeowner. This studio is accessible from the second level with a passage and door that provides privacy as well as an outdoor private entrance. Seller is leaving it fully furnished so it will be ready to go for the new owner!

Outdoors, a spacious deck invites you to relax amidst nature's tranquility, perfect for dining or entertaining. A 22' x 26' shop/boat storage area caters to outdoor enthusiasts, providing ample space for recreational vehicles, tools, or a boat for nearby lake adventures, less than 2 miles.

Wildlife enthusiasts will love the access to a private lake stocked with bass and crappie, making it a fishing paradise. High-speed DSL internet ensures connectivity in today's world.

In summary, this Sulphur, Oklahoma home offers comfort, natural beauty, and income potential. Its secluded location, modern amenities, and versatile studio  make it a unique opportunity, whether you seek a private retreat or an investment property. Experience the best of Sulphur living in this exceptional home.
